criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  AA parents (biological, grandparent, legal guardian) and their 8- to 11-year-old child
             residing in the same home.

          -  One overweight/obese parent (BMI ≥25 kg/m2) and child (≥ 85th% age-/sex-specific BMI).

          -  Parent at-risk for diabetes (American Diabetes Association risk test) AND HbA1c 5.7% -
             6.4%.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  child or parent has a history of T2DM or a screening HbA1c >6.4%;

          -  is taking glucose-lowering medications;

          -  is participating in a supervised weight loss program;

          -  is pregnant or breast feeding;

          -  has conditions limiting participation;

          -  has undergone weight loss surgery;

          -  is moving out-of-state within 6 months.

          -  If a parent becomes pregnant during the study, we will include only child data (index
             participant) in analyses
